<p>The fix for this issue is included in Office XP <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/download/details.aspx?familyid=1a8ce553-ab76-4a63-99da-b4ed914c1514&amp;displaylang=en" data-linktype="external">Service Pack2</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Reboot needed:</strong> No reboot is required if all Office applications are closed when the patch is applied.</p>
<p><strong>Patch can be uninstalled:</strong> No</p>
<p><strong>Superseded patches:</strong> None.</p>
<p><strong>Verifying patch installation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>General patch: Verify the file versions as discussed in Q322382.</li>
<li>Microsoft Project 2002 patch: Verify the file versions as discussed in Q328043.</li>
<li>Microsoft Project Server 2002 patches: Verify the file versions as discussed in Q328044.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Caveats:</strong></p>
<p>None</p>
<p><strong>Localization:</strong></p>
<p>Localized versions of this patch are available at the locations discussed in &quot;Patch Availability&quot;.</p>
<p><strong>Obtaining other security patches:</strong></p>
<p>Patches for other security issues are available from the following locations:</p>
<ul>
<li>Security patches are available from the <a href="http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=21129" data-linktype="external">Microsoft Download Center</a>, and can be most easily found by doing a keyword search for &quot;security_patch&quot;.</li>
